# Permutations MCP — Agent Rules (v0.0.9)

These rules govern how AI coding agents must interact with this codebase. The Permutations MCP server generates **32-chromosome design DNA** from SHA-256 hashes across a **14-tier biological complexity model** (abiotic → prokaryotic → protist → bryophyte → vascular_flora → invertebrate_fauna → ectotherm_fauna → endotherm_fauna → tribal → city_state → nation_state → empire → network → singularity). **No aesthetic values may be invented manually.**

This tool is a **design constitution generator**, not a code generator. It produces genome constraints, CSS tokens, and architecture direction. **You — the agent — write the actual code** from those constraints.

---

## Tool Workflow (8 tools, in order)

```
STEP 1  generate_design_genome    ← always start here
STEP 2  generate_design_brief     ← read before writing any code
STEP 3  generate_ecosystem        ← (optional) when building a component library
STEP 4  generate_civilization     ← (optional) when complexity ≥ 0.68
FINAL   validate_design           ← run before shipping any CSS/HTML

ALTERNATIVE  extract_genome_from_url  ← use instead of STEP 1 when you have a reference site
EXPORT       generate_formats         ← export tokens to Figma/Style Dictionary after STEP 1
ITERATE      update_design_genome     ← adjust chromosomes after STEP 1 ("make it warmer")
```

The response from `generate_design_genome` includes `suggested_next` — read it. It tells you exactly which tools to call next based on the genome's complexity.

---

## Rule 1 — Always Call The Engine First

Before creating any new UI component, page, section or design token, you MUST call `generate_design_genome`.

```json
{
  "tool": "generate_design_genome",
  "arguments": {
    "intent": "<describe the component or page in plain language>",
    "seed": "<project-name>-<component-name>-<timestamp>",
    "project_context": "<overarching brand or product narrative>",
    "brand_asset_paths": ["</absolute/path/to/logo.png>", "</absolute/path/to/brand-guidelines.pdf>"]
  }
}
```

`project_context` and `brand_asset_paths` are optional but improve accuracy.

Use `offline: true` to skip LLM semantic extraction and use hash-based inference — faster, no API cost, deterministic. Use when the intent is precise and sector detection is not needed.

**REQUIREMENT:** One LLM API key MUST be set (unless using `offline: true`): GROQ_API_KEY, OPENAI_API_KEY, ANTHROPIC_API_KEY, GEMINI_API_KEY, OPENROUTER_API_KEY, or HUGGINGFACE_API_KEY.

---

## Rule 2 — Read The Genome Report

Every `generate_design_genome` response includes a `genome_report` field — a markdown document explaining:
- Which sector was detected from your intent
- Which chromosomes were sequenced and their values
- What color constraints are in effect (including dark mode variants)
- The suggested workflow for what to call next

**Read this report before writing any code.** The genome is a black box without it.

---

## Rule 3 — Apply The Generated CSS Tokens

The genome response includes a `css` field — the full design token stylesheet. Inject this into your project:

- Copy CSS custom properties under `:root` into your `index.css` or global stylesheet
- Use `var(--color-primary)` for light mode, `var(--color-primary-interactive)` for dark mode buttons
- Use `var(--genome-easing)` and `var(--genome-duration)` for all animations
- Use `var(--color-surface-0)` through `--color-surface-3` for backgrounds

**Do not invent values not present in the genome.**

---

## Rule 4 — Respect Forbidden Patterns

The `genome.constraints.forbiddenPatterns` array contains patterns you are **strictly prohibited from using**.

Common examples:
| Pattern | What to avoid |
|---|---|
| `large_hero_images` | No full-bleed background images in hero sections |
| `scroll_animations` | No scroll-triggered fade/parallax effects |
| `bounce_animations` | No spring-easing on bouncy elements |
| `rounded_cards` | No heavily rounded cards (border-radius must be genome-defined) |
| `heavy_blur_effects` | No backdrop-filter or gaussian blur greater than genome intensity |
| `generous_whitespace` | No padding > genome-unit × 2 between sections |

Run `validate_design` before shipping to catch violations automatically.

---

## Rule 5 — Respect Required Patterns

The `genome.constraints.requiredPatterns` array contains patterns you **must implement**.

Common examples:
| Pattern | What to implement |
|---|---|
| `high_contrast_text` | All body text must meet the `minContrastRatio` from ch17_accessibility |
| `tabular_numerals` | All numbers must use `font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums` |
| `compact_base_spacing` | Use `genome-unit` (from ch2) as the base spacing unit everywhere |

---

## Rule 6 — Typography Must Use Genome Values

Do not invent font sizes. Use the values from `ch3_type_display` (headings) and `ch4_type_body` (body text):
- `text-display` for hero headings
- `text-h1`, `text-h2`, `text-h3` for hierarchy
- `text-body` for paragraphs
- `text-small` for captions and metadata

Do not use font families not defined in the genome.

---

## Rule 7 — Color Is Derived From The Genome

The primary color is defined by `ch5_color_primary.hex`. Never use hardcoded hex values.

Dark mode: use `ch5_color_primary.darkModeHex` (lightness 58–74%) for buttons and interactive elements on dark surfaces. The base `hex` (lightness 22–35%) is invisible on dark backgrounds.

Background colors come from `ch6_color_temp.surfaceStack`. Use `--color-surface-0` through `--color-surface-3`.

---

## Rule 8 — Motion Must Respect The Genome

Use `transition-timing-function: var(--genome-easing)` and `transition-duration: var(--genome-duration)` for all animations.
If `ch17_accessibility.respectMotionPreference` is `true`, wrap all animations with `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference)`.

---

## Rule 9 — Ecosystem And Civilization Return Specs, Not Code

`generate_ecosystem` returns a component hierarchy (microbial/flora/fauna) with prop contracts, containment relationships, and color treatments. **You write the components from these specs.** The tool does not generate TSX.

`generate_civilization` returns architecture direction: state topology, routing patterns, token inheritance. **You implement the architecture from these constraints.** The tool does not generate application files by default.

To opt into code generation: pass `generate_code: true` to `generate_civilization`. This is an explicit opt-in — default is `false`.

---

## Rule 10 — Validate Before Shipping

Always call `validate_design` with your final CSS and HTML before shipping. It checks:
- Forbidden pattern violations from the genome constraints
- Dark pattern detection (AI slop tells, generic shadow stacks, gradient text)
- Contrast and accessibility requirements

A `slop_score: 0` and `valid: true` is the target.

---

## When To Re-Run The Engine

- When starting a new feature area (e.g. switching from landing page to dashboard)
- When the user provides brand assets (logos, style guides)
- When the user changes the direction ("make it warmer", "change sector to fintech") — use `update_design_genome`
- Never re-run with the same seed for the same component unless you want deterministic regeneration
